<br>
Would this be a wise choice?<br>
<br>
I like using two of the same weapons in each hand. Not just for the cosmetic effect, but because it appears that a dual-wield at more predictable times when the weapons have equal speeds.<br>
<br>
Also, I hear that angled daggers have a spd of 2.2 -- is this true? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dajantor>Dajantor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#000000>(12/31/02 11:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Piercemaster weaponry choice</span><hr size=1> Yes, angled daggers have  speed of 2.2. <br>
<br>
Yes, upgrading to angled daggers would be a good choice. You should have diamondback when you're 25, and faster weapons with stun-styles is always a fun combination. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kianmacslann>Kian MacSlann</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(1/18/03 6:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Piercemaster weaponry choice</span><hr size=1> Funny... all the angled daggers I've been crafting have a speed of 3.0 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dajantor>Dajantor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#000000>(1/19/03 7:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Heh.</span><hr size=1> Got me on that one, I just checked it. ( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=paladinbrewer>Paladin Brewer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(1/20/03 3:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Piercemaster weaponry...</span><hr size=1> Im a Pierce specced Blademaster, and I prefer a Guarded Rapier in mainhand, and an angled in the offhand.  GR is slow, yes, but it will do more dmg over the same time interval. <p>Malkierr Brewer<br>
&lt;BR&gt;Blademaster of the 50th Season<br>
&lt;BR&gt;Guildmaster of Sword of the Dragon<br>
&lt;BR&gt;http://www.swordofthedragon.com<br>
&lt;BR&gt;&quot;It takes a hard stone, to make a sharp blade.&quot;<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=halbaradaglardin>Halbarad Aglardin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#000000>(1/24/03 7:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.arador.de/halklein.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Piercemaster weaponry...</span><hr size=1> Getting Guarded Rapiers/Angled Daggers before level 50 is a waste of money in my opinion.<br>
<br>
Dirks of the higher material have the same dps, can get a 5% higher bonus when enchanted, and cost only a small part of a Guarded Rapier/Angled Dagger combo of the lower material.<br>
<br>
just my two coppers. <p>==================<br>
