<br>
That's true, but don't dirks have a spd of like 2.3? I find that somewhat humorous. I think 3.0 spd is more what I'm looking for. Not too fast, not too slow. Angled daggers might cost more, but when cost isn't an issue, are they still the better choice?<br>
<br>
I'm not positive on how enchantment works in PvE. Occasionally I'll forget to enchant my weapons and not realize I haven't done so until I've outgrown them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=halbaradaglardin>Halbarad Aglardin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#000000>(3/1/03 2:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.arador.de/halklein.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wai~</span><hr size=1> Afaik, Bonus (enchantment) increases your chance to hit (weapons) or absorb (armor). This is the same in PvE and RvR I think.<br>
<br>
Well, I am happy for you if cost isn't an issue for you, but I always tell my customers below lvl 45 the dirk-angled dagger comparison.<br>
<br>
80% of them order a dirk pair then, because for them, cost is an issue <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If dirks are too fast, you could go with two stilettos (spd 2.6) or a rapier (spd 2.7)/stiletto combo.<br>
<br>
You would be 3-4 levels higher than the guarded rapier/angled dagger combo.<br>
<br>
On the way to 50, every weapon combo is viable, some are better suited for some mobs or personal play styles. There is no wrong combo (maybe guarded rapier/club combo with blades spec <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) so whatever works is right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
